{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"52156946-77fd-43f7-81cf-7e8a427b48f3","content":"Here's the setup:\n\n---\n\n**Workflow** (`.github/workflows/publish.yml`) — triggers on GitHub releases, packs your library, and pushes to nuget.org using OIDC (no API key needed). The key line is `permissions: id-token: write`.\n\n**On nuget.org**, you must register the trusted publisher:\n\n1. Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers** (or set it up before the first push under your account settings)\n2. Add a **GitHub Actions** publisher with:\n   - **Repository owner:** `myorg`\n   - **Repository:** `mylib`\n   - **Workflow:** `publish.yml`\n   - **Environment:** *(leave blank unless you use one)*\n\n**No `--api-key` is passed** to `dotnet nuget push` — NuGet.org authenticates via the OIDC token that GitHub Actions provides automatically when `id-token: write` is set.\n\n**To publish:** create a GitHub Release → the workflow runs → package appears on nuget.org.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6498ed16-864c-4a90-9217-b6052027e849","outputTokens":250,"requestId":"0401:2261B0:9FACCD:B9CB51:69F3FB0F"},"id":"53094eeb-5428-4b37-a53e-34fe0e292bcb","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:00:07.470Z","parentId":"cf6843bc-4479-4f12-a1d6-69e0b9bfdabd"}
